        <att name="title">Water Property Measurements from the Bute Inlet Ocean Observing Station (BIOOS) Wirewalker, Bute Inlet, BC, Canada (Provisional)</att>
        <att name="summary">Bute Inlet, a prominent fjord on the British Columbia coast, has been a site for high-resolution oceanographic profiling through the Bute Inlet Ocean Observing Station (BIOOS). A Canadian Pacific Robotic Ocean Observing Facility (C-PROOF) Wirewalker wave-powered profiling instrument is deployed on a mooring in the central fjord, collecting vertical profiles of conductivity, temperature, pressure, and dissolved oxygen concentration. Only upcast profiles are presented in this dataset. This data contribution consists of provisional measurements spanning the current year and has not undergone full quality control.</att>
